TITLE: Editorial Roundup: United States
SUMMARY: Excerpts from recent editorials in the United States and abroad:

TITLE: Magnitude 6.4 earthquake shakes parts of Northern California
SUMMARY: Officials say a strong earthquake in a rural stretch of Northern California has cut off power to 70,000 people and damaged roads and homes

TITLE: EPA to tighten nitrogen oxide limits for new heavy trucks
SUMMARY: In a little over four years, new heavy truck makers will have to cut harmful nitrogen oxide pollution more than 80% under standards released Tuesday by the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency

TITLE: Wells Fargo to pay $3.7B over consumer law violations
SUMMARY: Consumer banking giant Wells Fargo agreed to pay $3.7 billion to settle charges that it harmed consumers by charging illegal fees and interest on auto loans and mortgages, as well as incorrectly applied overdraft fees against savings and checking accounts

TITLE: Police, FBI plan update on deadly Indiana mall shooting
SUMMARY: Five months after a 20-year-old man fatally shot three people at a suburban Indianapolis mall, police and the FBI could shed light this week on the gunman’s motive

TITLE: Wells Fargo to pay $3.7B over consumer loan violations
SUMMARY: Consumer banking giant Wells Fargo is being ordered to pay $3.7 billion in fines and refunds to customers by U.S. government regulators, the largest fine to date against the bank

TITLE: 2nd Iowa man arrested in street race that killed 4-year-old
